Johannesburg is the highest rated African city with Lagos in Nigeria at the bottom of the list. LONDON - London has been named as the world's greatest city in a new survey which saw Johannesburg in 23rd place behind Moscow. The world's leading cities were rated on a variety of factors. Culture, entertainment, infrastructure, health and the general happiness of residents were all taken into account. More than 5,000 well-educated, high-net-worth adults from 16 countries around the world took part in the survey for accountancy firm Pricewaterhouse Coopers. London came out top with Paris and New York in second and third place respectively. Johannesburg is the highest rated African city with Lagos in Nigeria at the bottom of the list.